Task: 11
Title: OpenAI streaming adapter and SSE encoder
Phase: 3
Route: full
Slice: Streaming Synthesis + Timeouts
Dependencies: 09
Scope: Implement stream() on OpenAiChatAdapter using the openai SDK's client.chat.completions.stream() convenience method, wiring AbortSignal from ChatRequest.options.signal through to the SDK call. Create the OpenAI SSE encoder module: encodeOpenAiSSE() maps FusionStreamEvent to wire-format SSE strings (content_delta → chat.completion.chunk JSON, done → [DONE]), and encodeKeepAlive() emits SSE comment lines for progress stages. The OpenAiChatAdapter modification is a cross-phase revisit (originally created Task 04) to add streaming — the port contract is now extended with stream().
Acceptance Criteria: AC-10 (partial — SSE encoding), AC-12 (partial — AbortController wiring)
NFRs: NFR-1, NFR-3
Gate Criteria: Phase 3 Gate 1 (SSE encoder ready), Phase 3 Gate 2 (AbortController wired)
Files:
  - src/infrastructure/outbound/llm/openai-chat-adapter.ts (MODIFY) — Implement stream() using openai SDK client.chat.completions.stream(); wire AbortSignal from ChatRequest.options.signal; yield ChatStreamEvent tokens from SDK stream events
  - src/infrastructure/inbound/http/openai/sse-encoder.ts (CREATE) — encodeOpenAiSSE(event: FusionStreamEvent): string | null — maps content_delta → chat.completion.chunk JSON, done → [DONE]; encodeKeepAlive(stage: string): string — emits SSE comment lines
